The paper presents a graph rewriting system that can be used as a model of computation in algorithmic chemistry. This suggests that the paper could be relevant to several sub-categories, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for its potential use in modeling complex systems, discrete mathematics (cs.DM) for its focus on graph rewriting, programming languages (cs.PL) for its use of local moves as rewrites, systems and control (cs.SY) for its potential use in modeling chemical systems, and computational complexity (cs.CC) for its Turing completeness.
